<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/680</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-17T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            17, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>312. Your 474, October 13, 7 p.m. As you have already been advised,
                                United States, Great Britain, and France are sharing joint expense
                                of rationing Murmansk and Archangel districts for the winter. The
                                shipments you mention, although the purchase was undertaken by the
                                British, apparently represent supplies for payment of which
                                Government of United States will assume one third
                                responsibility.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>